IRS990.Desc: TO ORGANIZE ALL WORKERS FOR THE ECONOMIC, MORAL AND SOCIAL ADVANCEMENT OF THEIR CONDITION AND STATUS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE LOCAL IS REQUIRED TO EVALUATE ITS TAX POSITIONS AND DISCLOSE THE AMOUNT OF TAX LIABILITIES IF THE LOCAL HAS TAKEN AN UNCERTAIN POSITION THAT MORE LIKELY THAN NOT WOULD NOT BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION BY TAX AUTHORITIES. THE LOCAL IS SUBJECT TO ROUTINE AUDITS BY TAXING JURISDICTIONS; HOWEVER, THERE ARE CURRENTLY NO AUDITS FOR ANY TAX PERIODS IN PROGRESS.

GrantsOtherAsstToIndivInUSGrp.GrantTypeTxt: CONTRIBUTIONS FROM SOLIDARITY FUND (NEEDY MEMBER RELIEF)

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE EXECUTIVE BOARD CAREFULLY REVIEWS ALL REQUESTS FOR DONATIONS AND GRANTS PRIOR TO THEIR APPROVAL AND DISBURSEMENT. APPROVAL IS GRANTED ONLY TO REPUTABLE ORGANIZATIONS WHO HAVE SATISFIED THE BOARD'S DUE DILIGENCE. THE BOARD PERFORMS NO SUBSEQUENT MONITORING OF THE USE OF THE DONATION OR GRANT. ALL RECORDS REGARDING THE DISBURSEMENT OF FUNDS ARE MAINTAINED AT THE LOCAL'S OFFICE.
THE ORGANIZATION HAS ATTEMPTED NUMEROUS TIMES, UNSUCCESSFULLY, TO OBTAIN THE MISSING INFORMATION NECESSARY TO COMPLETE PART II OF SCHEDULE I.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE LOCAL UNION'S GENERAL MEMBERSHIP IS COMPRISED OF INDIVIDUALS WHO HAVE EXECUTED A WRITTEN APPLICATION FOR MEMERSHIP, HAVE TENDERED THE APPROPRIATE INITIATION FEES AND HAVE BEEN ACCEPTED INTO THE LOCAL.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MEMBERS WITH VOTING RIGHTS AND CURRENT IN THEIR DUES PAYMENTS ARE ELIGIBILE TO VOTE FOR INDIVIDUALS WHICH COMPRISE THE EXECUTIVE BOARD (GOVERNING BODY) OF THE LOCAL UNION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE GENERAL MEMBERSHIP APPROVES CHANGES TO THE GOVERNING DOCUMENTS ALONG WITH SIGNIFICANT DECISIONS MADE BY THE EXECUTIVE BOARD OF THE LOCAL UNION (GOVERNING BODY) AT PERIODIC MEMBERSHIP MEETINGS CONVENED AS REQUIRED BY INTERNATIONAL AND LOCAL GOVERNING DOCUMENTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 8B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE LOCAL HAS NO COMMITTEES WITH THE AUTHORITY TO ACT ON BEHALF OF THE EXECUTIVE BOARD (GOVERNING BODY).

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ENTIRE EXECUTIVE BOARD (GOVERNING BODY) REVIEWS AND APPROVES THE FORM 990 PRIOR TO SUBMISSION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE SALARIES OF BUSINESS MANAGER-FINANCIAL SECRETARY, OFFICERS, AND KEY EMPLOYEES ARE SET BY UNION BYLAWS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE GOVERNING DOCUMENTS AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST AT THE LOCAL UNION OFFICE.
